### Variáveis globais
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@token = COLE_O_ACCESS_TOKEN_AQUI
@photoId = COLE_O_PHOTO_ID_AQUI


### --- Perfil do Casamento ---

### 1. Criar casamento
# Fluxo mínimo: bride_name, groom_name, date, location.
# O slug é gerado automaticamente (ex: "ana-e-joao").
# Retorna 409 se já existe um casamento para essa conta.
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/wedding
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bride_name": "Ana",
  "groom_name": "João",
  "date": "2025-12-20",
  "location": "Buffet Royal"
}


### 1b. Criar casamento completo (com campos opcionais e links)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/wedding
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bride_name": "Ana",
  "groom_name": "João",
  "date": "2025-12-20",
  "time": "18:00",
  "location": "Buffet Royal",
  "city": "São Paulo",
  "state": "SP",
  "description": "Nossa história começou em 2020...",
  "links": [
    { "label": "Buffet Royal", "url": "https://buffetroyal.com.br" },
    { "label": "Fotógrafo", "url": "https://instagram.com/foto" }
  ]
}


### 2. Consultar casamento
# Retorna o perfil completo com fotos e links.
# Retorna 404 se o casal ainda não criou o casamento.
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/wedding
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 3. Editar casamento (parcial)
# Envie apenas os campos que deseja alterar.
# Links omitidos = mantém existentes.
# Links com [] = limpa todos os links.
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/v1/wedding
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "location": "Chácara das Flores"
}


### 3b. Editar com múltiplos campos
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/v1/wedding
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bride_name": "Ana Paula",
  "groom_name": "João Pedro",
  "date": "2026-01-10",
  "time": "20:00",
  "location": "Espaço Nobre",
  "city": "Campinas",
  "state": "SP",
  "description": "Uma celebração inesquecível"
}


### 3c. Substituir links
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/v1/wedding
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "links": [
    { "label": "Site do casamento", "url": "https://meusite.com" },
    { "label": "Lista de presentes", "url": "https://amazon.com.br/lista" }
  ]
}


### 3d. Limpar todos os links
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/v1/wedding
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "links": []
}


### --- Fotos ---

### 4. Upload de foto
# Envie via multipart/form-data com campo "photo".
# Formatos aceitos: .jpg, .jpeg, .png, .webp (máx 10MB).
# Use curl ou ferramentas que suportem multipart para este endpoint:
#
#   curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/v1/wedding/photos \
#     -H "Authorization: Bearer SEU_TOKEN" \
#     -F "photo=@/caminho/para/foto.jpg"
#
# O VS Code REST Client não suporta upload de arquivo local nativo.
# Veja wedding-upload.http para a requisição multipart.
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/wedding/photos
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="photo"; filename="test.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./test-photo.jpg
--boundary--


### 5. Remover foto
# Substitua @photoId pelo ID retornado no upload.
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/v1/wedding/photos/{{photoId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### --- Cenários de erro ---

### Criar sem autenticação → 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/wedding
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bride_name": "Ana",
  "groom_name": "João",
  "date": "2025-12-20",
  "location": "Local"
}


### Criar sem campos obrigatórios → 422
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/wedding
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bride_name": "Ana"
}


### Criar com data inválida → 422
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/wedding
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bride_name": "Ana",
  "groom_name": "João",
  "date": "20/12/2025",
  "location": "Local"
}


### Criar casamento duplicado → 409
# Rode após já ter criado o casamento na mesma conta.
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/wedding
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bride_name": "Ana",
  "groom_name": "João",
  "date": "2025-12-20",
  "location": "Outro local"
}


### Remover foto inexistente → 404
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/v1/wedding/photos/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
